body:
## Rationale

Signature gear pages at `/drummers/<slug>/signature/<gearSlug>` are **sitemapped at priority 0.85** (`api/sitemap.js:470`), but have **no SSR meta handler** in `api/meta/[...path].js`. Generic `<title>MetalForge</title>` is served to crawlers — this kills CTR for high-purchase-intent queries like "joey jordison pearl signature snare", "lars ulrich paiste rude china".

Currently 2 pages sitemapped:
- `/drummers/joey-jordison/signature/joey-jordison-pearl-signature-snare`
- `/drummers/lars-ulrich/signature/lars-ulrich-paiste-rude-china`

3 more planned (commented out in `api/sitemap.js:235–238`): Danny Carey Paiste Giant Beat Gongs, Mario Duplantier Tama Starphonic Bronze, Gene Hoglan — will need the same handler when added.

These are product-focused pages with affiliate potential. The `SIGNATURE_GEAR` object in `packages/frontend/data/signatureGear.js` carries complete name, model, brand, drummerId, category, hero tagline, and story content.

## Files to touch

**`api/meta/[...path].js`** — add regex handler:

```js
const sigGearMatch = path.match(/^\/drummers\/([^/]+)\/signature\/([^/]+)\/?$/);
if (sigGearMatch) {
  const [, drummerSlug, gearSlug] = sigGearMatch;
  const gear = SIGNATURE_GEAR[gearSlug];
  const drummer = getDrummerBySlug(drummerSlug);
  if (gear && drummer) {
    return {
      title: `${gear.fullName} — ${drummer.name}'s Signature Snare | MetalForge`,
      description: `${gear.hero.tagline}. Full specs, story, and pricing for ${drummer.name}'s ${gear.name} (${gear.model}).`,
      articleSchema: JSON.stringify({
        '@context': 'https://schema.org',
        '@graph': [
          {
            '@type': 'Product',
            name: gear.fullName,
            model: gear.model,
            brand: { '@type': 'Brand', name: gear.brand },
            description: gear.hero.subtitle,
          },
          {
            '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
            itemListElement: [
              { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: BASE_URL },
              { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: drummer.name, item: `${BASE_URL}/drummers/${drummerSlug}` },
              { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 3, name: gear.name, item: `${BASE_URL}/drummers/${drummerSlug}/signature/${gearSlug}` },
            ],
          },
        ],
      }),
      url: `${BASE_URL}/drummers/${drummerSlug}/signature/${gearSlug}`,
    };
  }
}
```

Import: add `SIGNATURE_GEAR` to the imports from `../packages/frontend/data/signatureGear.js`.

## Quality gate

- SSR title includes gear full name + drummer name
- Product schema with `model`, `brand.name` emitted in SSR
- BreadcrumbList has 3 levels (Home → Drummer → Gear name)
- Generic fallback NOT returned when `gearSlug` is known

## Estimated uplift

Targets purchase-intent queries: "joey jordison pearl signature snare", "lars ulrich paiste china", "pearl jj1365n". These are bottom-of-funnel with affiliate click potential.

## Verify

1. `curl -s https://metalforge.io/api/meta/drummers/joey-jordison/signature/joey-jordison-pearl-signature-snare | grep -i title` — should contain "Pearl Joey Jordison Signature Snare"
2. Check JSON-LD `@type: Product` present in SSR HTML
3. Check BreadcrumbList 3 levels
4. `curl -s https://metalforge.io/api/meta/drummers/lars-ulrich/signature/lars-ulrich-paiste-rude-china | grep -i "rude\|ulrich"` — should match
5. Generic fallback NOT returned for these 2 slugs

## Done

`/drummers/<slug>/signature/<gearSlug>` returns keyword-matched SSR meta + Product + BreadcrumbList JSON-LD. Works for both existing and future signature gear pages.
